trans-unit.source: The IAccIdentity and all of its exposed members are part of a managed wrapper for the Component Object Model (COM) <xref uid="langword_csharp_IAccIdentity" name="IAccIdentity" href=""></xref> interface.

For more information about IAccIdentity, see the documentation for `IAccIdentity::GetIdentityString` in the Microsoft Active Accessibility documentation in the MSDN library at http://msdn.microsoft.com/library.

The <xref href="Accessibility.IAccIdentity"></xref> and all of its exposed members are part of a managed wrapper for the Component Object Model (COM) <xref uid="langword_csharp_IAccIndentity" name="IAccIndentity" href=""></xref> interface.

For more information about GetIdentityString, see the documentation for `IAccIdentity::GetIdentityString` in the Microsoft Active Accessibility documentation in the MSDN library at http://msdn.microsoft.com/library.
Specifies which child of the IAccessible object the caller wants to identify.
Address of a variable that receives a pointer to a callee-allocated identity string.

The callee allocates the identity string using <xref uid="langword_csharp_CoTaskMemAlloc" name="CoTaskMemAlloc" href=""></xref>; the caller must release the identity string by using <xref uid="langword_csharp_CoTaskMemFree" name="CoTaskMemFree" href=""></xref> when finished.
Address of a variable that receives the length, in bytes, of the callee-allocated identity string.
